The Petroleum Products Pricing Regulatory Agency today disclosed that the price of Premium Motor Spirit, also known as petrol, has hit N212.6 per litre. The PPPRA template follows the increasing price of crude at the international market as well as instability in exchange rate. But the latest template may witness protest by most Nigerians who are battling hard to survive in a battered economy being supervised by the administration of Muhammad Buhari. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Nigerians are specifically worried over the cost of energy at a time the crude oil price is on the rise and the growing global campaign for energy transition. The Nigerian Labour Congress had yesterday embarked in nationwide protest over the planned exclusion of the national minimum wage for legislative exclusive list Strong-arm Tactics, Distortions Will Not Resolve Minimum Wage Logjam-DG PGF Okowa Congratulates NFF President, Amaju Pinnick On FIFA Seat Victory The monthly template of the agency said petrol is expected to sell at a lower retail price of N209.61 and at an upper retail price of N212.61. Nigerian marketers usually use the upper band for pump price. The expected ex-depot price, according to the PPPRA template,is N206.42, while the landing cost is N189.61. Following the current ex-depot price at N206.42 per litre, the March template shows that the landing cost for petrol per litre is N189.61. The Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation had earlier assured that petrol price would remain static in March to allow smooth negotiations between the government and labour unions.